Nymph:
Triocellate, anterior ocellus highly reduced. Compound eyes small, only 20 % of lateral head length. General color reddish brown, without obvious pattern (
Figs. 7–9A
). Pronotum smooth on surface, completely fringed with long bristles along lateral margins. Legs with sparse dorsal fringes on femora and tibiae but rather heavily armed with stout setae. Thoracic and anal gills well developed; more than 5 branches present on each gill (
Fig. 8
). Paraprocts large, apex finger-like and pointed (
Figs. 8G
).
